From e1ec8f0244b3ee13239504e6a081963374e2663f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ivan Leon <ivan@sharpe.com>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 02:11:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Stereo: copy LonePair virtual edges in 'copy unmatched from
 R1' branch
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The RC::Visitor::Stereo::handleBoth visitor's "second-to-first subgraph"
case at lines 388-422 walks unmatched virtual edges from R1's stereo
embedding into the result. The LonePair / Radical branch at lines
404-407 hits MOD_ABORT unconditionally, but the same file's
copyAllFromSide lambda at lines 94-101 handles LonePair correctly:

    case lib::Stereo::EmbeddingEdge::Type::LonePair:
        // offsets should be corrected somewhere else
        data.edges.emplace_back(-1, ..::LonePair, emb.cat);
        break;

Mirroring that pattern here unblocks any substrate carrying an amine N
at degree 3+: Stereo/Inference.hpp:276 calls addLonePairs(v, 1) for
those, the DG Rule strategy at Rule.cpp:166-172 wraps the substrate as
a one-sided rule, RC::Super composes it with the user rule under
LabelSettings.withStereo=true, and finalize reaches the LonePair branch
on every rule application -- not only under explicit rcParallel/rcSub.

The Radical case keeps its MOD_ABORT (TODO) but now has the dead-code
emplace_back below it for symmetry with line 100-101.

Reproducer:

    import mod
    mod.config.io.useLabelSettings = True
    ls = mod.LabelSettings(mod.LabelType.Term,
                           mod.LabelRelation.Specialisation,
                           mod.LabelRelation.Specialisation)
    g = mod.Graph.fromSMILES("CCN")
    r = mod.Rule.fromGMLString(open("macrolactamization.gml").read())
    mod.DG(graphDatabase=[g], labelSettings=ls).build().execute(
        mod.addSubset(g) >> r)

Without this patch: MOD_ABORT at Stereo.hpp:406.
With this patch: DG construction completes; LonePair virtual edges
flow through to the composed rule's stereo conf as expected.

Bug surfaced by MØD-MacroCert Workstream F (ascomylactam A target
requires stereo enforcement on 12 sp3 centers). Full root-cause
analysis at docs/mod_abort_investigation.md in the macrocert repo.
---
 libs/libmod/src/mod/lib/RC/Visitor/Stereo.hpp | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/libs/libmod/src/mod/lib/RC/Visitor/Stereo.hpp b/libs/libmod/src/mod/lib/RC/Visitor/Stereo.hpp
index 8eff0ef..3a365fd 100644
--- a/libs/libmod/src/mod/lib/RC/Visitor/Stereo.hpp
+++ b/libs/libmod/src/mod/lib/RC/Visitor/Stereo.hpp
@@ -402,8 +402,18 @@ public:
 							for(const auto &emb: conf) {
 								switch(emb.type) {
 								case lib::Stereo::EmbeddingEdge::Type::LonePair:
+									// Copy lone-pair virtual edges through unchanged.
+									// Mirrors the LonePair case in copyAllFromSide above (lines 94-97).
+									// Without this, any substrate with an amine N at degree 3+ aborts
+									// under LabelSettings.withStereo=true via the addLonePairs(v, 1)
+									// injection in Stereo/Inference.hpp.
+									// offsets should be corrected somewhere else
+									data.edges.emplace_back(-1, lib::Stereo::EmbeddingEdge::Type::LonePair, emb.cat);
+									break;
 								case lib::Stereo::EmbeddingEdge::Type::Radical:
-									MOD_ABORT;
+									MOD_ABORT; // TODO (kept from upstream; matches the Radical TODO at line 99)
+									// offsets should be corrected somewhere else
+									data.edges.emplace_back(-1, lib::Stereo::EmbeddingEdge::Type::Radical, emb.cat);
 									break;
 								case lib::Stereo::EmbeddingEdge::Type::Edge:
 									const auto &gInput = get_graph(glSide);
